{"questionId":"6040","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A ray diagram for a converging lens is shown. The object is labelled O and the image is&nbsp;labelled I.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/65dad956a37a1c2cb7ab8f88daeeae949e6b653e.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Using the ray diagram,</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>determine the focal length of the lens.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>constructs ray parallel to principal axis and then to image position</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>u = 8 cm and v = 24 cm and lens formula</p>\n<p>6 <strong>«</strong>cm<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>eg:&nbsp;<img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4770/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_08.38.23.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/08.a.i/M\"></em></p>\n<p><em>Allow answers in the range of 5.6 to 6.4 cm</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6040","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.8a.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"determine the focal length of the lens.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)","C.1 – Introduction to imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}